Since 2017 until today I am on the board of the club for entrepreneurship in Karlsruhe Innovate e.V. After almost two years at SAP in the Sustainability New Ventures Team I got to know corporate´s struggle with innovation and empowering employees to become active themselves. 

These experiences led me to where I am today. I made it my mission to support Open Innovation and ccreate strong local innovation communities and making them accessible for everyone interested from everywhere of the globe.  Of course providing ALL necessary information and enabling efficient information exchange is key to create a new open innovation ecosystem.
_source.focussingon_text: Eventually, I am in the process of founding my own startup in the field of Open Innovation. Breaking borders of fragmented, local ecosystems and making them available to external Investors and Stakeholders will be one of the core challenges to solve on our way.  Dealflow, Cooperation Opportiunities and potential customers shall all be openly connected to enable serendipity, collaboration and eventually Innovation.

Robert is responsible for the Porsche Secondment Program, in which Prospective Porsche managers complete a two-week executive internship at APX. _source.aboutme_text:
Teddy is Head of Venture Development and Investor at APX. He aims to help change the world by magnifying our founders’ potential. In his day-to-day life, Teddy identifies ways in which he and his colleagues can best support our founders – with the help of a little engineered serendipity.

Before joining APX, Teddy lived different lives. He worked in strategic finance at Wayfair, invested in early-stage companies at Mustard Seed Impact, worked in finance at BlackRock, conducted clinical research, played the violin, and went to college a couple of times (after dropping out to work on a social enterprise). Most recently, Teddy had a fortuitous conversation with Henric, including a chat about music, and ended up returning to early-stage investing with APX.

Throughout his meandering experiences, Teddy continues to love learning and reading. And although he says he’s a ‘natural introvert’, he’s been on the radio and played the violin on stage with Jack Black. Surprisingly talkative and a self-styled philosopher, Teddy welcomes weird, deep conversations.
